  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To evaluate the effects of CO2 inhalation and acetazolamide treatment on exercise-induced
      periodic breathing in patients with chronic stable heart failure.

      Patients will be given CO2 (2%) during a constant workload exercise. Patients will be also
      evaluated by maximal cardiopulmonary exercise test without and with acetazolamide acute and
      chronic treatment.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
